     <div type="notice_to_the_reader">
   <pb n="95" facs="56"/>
   <head>An Aduertisement to the Reader.</head>
   <p>THe Errors of the <hi>Appealer</hi> are of three sorts, <hi>Po<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>pish,
Arminian,</hi> and of a third kinde, <hi>multi-for<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>miter
deformes.</hi> Of the first sort I haue giuen
thee a taste: Of the second thou shalt haue a Synopsis in
the Tablet ensuing: The third thou shalt finde in the Writ
of Errour. In all kindes I haue pretermitted some, <hi>Non
amore erroris, sed errore amoris: Not for any loue I
beare to his errors, but through an error of loue.</hi> Part<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ly
because I hope they are rather slips in his pen, than
downfalls in his iudgement: partly also because they are
discouered by others; whose writings had I seene before
my papers were ingaged in the Presse: <hi>Aiax hic meus in
spongiam incubuisset.</hi>
   </p>
</div>
